{"title": "Follow Your Nose", "content": "For humans, the sense of smell is one of the main ways we are drawn to food, so this naturally shows up a lot in fiction.\n\nIn comedic or cartoony situations, a character will be shown being physically lifted off the ground and floating toward the source of a delicious smell. In older Looney Tunes-style shorts the vapors of scent will often be clearly visible, physics aside, and sometimes the vapor will actually develop hands that will lift the character.\n\nVillains will sometimes build a trap around this trope and ensnare an unsuspecting hungry person.\n\nOften an example of Visible Odor. Compare The Nose Knows.", "url": "https://tvtropes.org/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/FollowYourNose", "media_links": ["/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/WesternAnimation/ClassicDisneyShorts", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/WesternAnimation/Futurama", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/WesternAnimation/LooneyTunes", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Manga/XxxHolic", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Anime/MaiHime", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Anime/WolfsRain", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Manga/OnePiece", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Manga/BakiTheGrappler", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Anime/YuGiOh", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Animation/MotuPatlu", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Animation/YamuchasKungFuAcademy", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/WesternAnimation/SpiderManIntoTheSpiderVerse", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Anime/SpiritedAway", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Webcomic/KarateBears", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Webcomic/Sinfest", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/WesternAnimation/TomAndJerry", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/WesternAnimation/MickeyMouse", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/WesternAnimation/Futurama", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/WesternAnimation/TheFlintstones", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/WesternAnimation/ChipNDaleRescueRangers", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/WesternAnimation/RenAndStimpy", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/WesternAnimation/DuckTales1987", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Franchise/ScoobyDoo", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/WesternAnimation/APupNamedScoobyDoo", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/WesternAnimation/Freakazoid", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/WesternAnimation/TheSimpsons", "/pmw